        </h1>
        <div class="tips-content">
            <h2 style="color: white;">1. Research the Company</h2>
            <p>Before your interview, thoroughly research the company's background, values, products, and recent achievements. This knowledge will impress the interviewer and show your genuine interest in the company.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">2. Practice Mock Interviews</h2>
            <p>Conduct mock interviews with friends or career counselors to gain confidence and refine your responses to common interview questions. Recording yourself can be helpful for self-assessment.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">3. Dress Professionally</h2>
            <p>Choose appropriate professional attire that aligns with the company's dress code. A well-groomed appearance leaves a positive first impression.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">4. Highlight Your Skills</h2>
            <p>During the interview, showcase your skills and experiences that are relevant to the job you are applying for. Provide concrete examples of your achievements.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">5. Ask Thoughtful Questions</h2>
            <p>Prepare thoughtful questions to ask the interviewer. This demonstrates your genuine interest and enthusiasm for the position.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">6. Body Language Matters</h2>
            <p>Pay attention to your body language; maintain eye contact, offer a firm handshake, and exhibit positive body posture. It conveys confidence and professionalism.</p>
      
            <h2 style="color: white;">7. Follow Up with a Thank-You Note</h2>
            <p>Send a personalized thank-you email or note to the interviewer within 24 hours of the interview. Express your appreciation for the opportunity and reiterate your interest in the position.</p>
